<h2>View reports</h2>

<p>COMPASS provides various reports to help you understand project and delivery status. To view reports:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Click on <strong>Reports</strong> in the top navigation menu</li>
    <li>Select the type of report you want to view:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>My reports</strong> - Reports for projects you're involved with</li>
            <li><strong>All DDT</strong> - Complete delivery, digital and technology report</li>
            <li><strong>Flagship projects</strong> - Report on flagship projects</li>
            <li><strong>Accessibility report</strong> - Accessibility issues and statements</li>
            <li><strong>Business area reports</strong> - Reports filtered by business area</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Use filters to narrow down the data you want to see</li>
    <li>Export reports if needed using the export options</li>
</ol>

<h3>Report types</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>My reports</strong> - Personalised view of your projects and their status</li>
    <li><strong>Portfolio reports</strong> - Overview of all projects across the organisation</li>
    <li><strong>Specialised reports</strong> - Focused reports on specific areas like accessibility or flagship projects</li>
</ul>

<p>Reports are updated in real-time based on the latest project data in COMPASS.</p>

